<div class="text-wrap">
  <h4>Takeaways</h4>
  <p>
    Referencing <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flow_(psychology)">Flow</a>
    as a guideline for the emotions users need to experience during the set up
    process, I learned a few things that are important for users in all kinds
    of interactions:
  </p>
  <h6>Experiencing feedback</h6>
  <p>
    Providing immediate feedback after users make decisions or advance forward
    in the flow communicates if their decisions will help them achieve the
    outcome they want and provide a sense of accomplishment.
  </p>
  <h6>Feeling Confident in one's ability</h6>
  <p>
   It's important that the user experiences a balance between the challenge of
   the difficulty of the taks and their technical ability to complete the task.
  </p>
  <h6>Eliminate distractions</h6>
  <p>
    If the user is in a state of flow, obstacles and challenges that come up
    outside of the immediate flow feel easier to overcome.
  </p>
